==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''*falwo-, falwa-'', from Indo-European ''*pel-''.

Cognate with Old Saxon [[falu]] (Dutch [[vaal]]), Old High German [[falo]] (German [[fahl]]), Old Norse [[fǫlr]].  The common Germanic is cognate with Latin [[pallere]] and Greek [[πολιός]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fæalu/

